{
  "text": "There are several models for NMT of MRLs which are designed to deal with morphological complexities. [CITATION_1] and adapted the factored machine translation approach to neural models. Morphological annotations can be treated as extra factors in such models. [CITATION_2] proposed a model to handle very large vocabularies. [CITATION_3] addressed the problem of rare words and OOVs with the help of a post-translation phase to exchange unknown tokens with their potential translations. used subword units for NMT. The model relies on frequent subword units instead of words. Costa-juss\u00e0 and Fonollosa (2016) designed a model for translating from MRLs. The model encodes source words with a convolutional module proposed by [CITATION_4] . Each word is represented by a convolutional combination of its characters.",
